        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 1:35PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 135 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Edwardsville, or near Heflin, moving south at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Heflin, Ranburne, Fruithurst, Edwardsville, Muscadine, Abernathy,
Mars Hills, Hollis Crossroads, Sweetwater Lake, Coleman Lake And
Campground, Trickem, Lake Cleburne, I 20 Welcome Center, Liberty
Hill, Micaville, Oak Level, and Chalafinnee.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
